- cs.ET (Emerging Technologies): The paper discusses a new way of modeling entanglement in quantum computing, which can be considered an emerging technology in the field. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages): The paper presents a formal axiomatization of entanglement as a kind of parallelism, which can be seen as a programming language construct. 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science): The paper uses logical reasoning to establish the soundness and completeness of the axiomatization. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity): The paper may have implications for the computational complexity of quantum algorithms that use entanglement. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper discusses the merge operation of entanglement, which can be seen as a kind of data structure operation.
